The paper deals with query optimization and cardinality estimation in databases, which falls under the category of computer science databases (cs.DB). The use of deep learning and specialized schemes for representing SQL queries suggests that the paper may also be relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of containment rates and experiments with a real-world database, which may make it relevant to cryptography and security (cs.CR) and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
